SuccessTeam.name: SuccessTeam
SuccessTeam.description: Records details about a success team in Salesforce Scheduler.

AccountId.description: The account associated with the success team.

CanSelfSchedule.description: Specifies whether the success team can be self scheduled (true) or not (false).

CaseRecordTypeId.description: The case record type associated with the success team.

DefaultUnassignedCaseTeam.description: The case team associated with the success team.

IsActive.description: Specifies whether the success team is active (true) or not (false).

IsLocked.description: Indicates whether the record is locked (true) or not (false).

LastReferencedDate.description: The timestamp when the current user last accessed this record, a record related to this record, or a list view.

LastViewedDate.description: The timestamp when the current user last viewed this record or list view. If this value is null, the user might have only accessed this record or list view (LastReferencedDate) but not viewed it.

MayEdit.description: Indicates whether the record can be edited (true) or not (false).

Name.description: The name of the success team.

OwnerId.description: The user who owns this record.

ResourceAssignmentType.description: Specifies the type of resource assignment for appointment scheduling.
